## Detailed Gap Analysis

### PART 1: Classroom & Seating Infrastructure Management

> [!NOTE]
> The physical infrastructure layer is beautifully built, premium in appearance, and matches the modern visual guidelines.

#### 1. Classroom Management
* **Database Schema (Drizzle):** Fully implemented in [schema.ts](file:///p:/02_projects/mono/apps/erp/app/lib/schema.ts#L605-L620). Handles `roomCode` (e.g. G1, F2), `buildingName`, `floor`, `lectureCapacity`, `description`, and `isActive`.
* **Classrooms Page:** Fully implemented at [app/classes/page.tsx](file:///p:/02_projects/mono/apps/erp/app/app/classes/page.tsx). Renders a data table with standard actions, floor color badges, and interactive KPI summaries (Total Classes, Physical Capacity, Active Benches, Layouts Configured/Unconfigured).
* **Creation Drawer:** Operates perfectly using `CreateClassroomDrawer` via `@heroui/react` overlay triggers.

#### 2. Classroom Layout Designer (BookMyShow-Style)
* **View Layout Page:** Fully implemented at [app/classes/\[slug\]/page.tsx](file:///p:/02_projects/mono/apps/erp/app/app/classes/%5Bslug%5D/page.tsx). Renders a stage/board indicator and maps cells based on coordinate grid coordinates (`gridX`, `gridY`). Row lettering (A, B, C) and column numbering (Col 1, Col 2) are fully functional.
* **Layout Editor Page:** Fully implemented at [app/classes/\[slug\]/edit/page.tsx](file:///p:/02_projects/mono/apps/erp/app/app/classes/%5Bslug%5D/edit/page.tsx). 
  * *Add Bench:* Clicking standard dashed `+` empty grids immediately instantiates a bench.
  * *Remove Bench:* Clicking the hover `X` button cleanses the grid coordinate.
  * *Capacity Controls:* Bench cells contain `+` and `−` controls modifying `maxStudents` (caps at 1–4 per bench) inline.
  * *Auto-Generate Tool:* Wizard utility allows setting a dynamic grid dimension (e.g. $4 \times 5$) and default bench capacity to seed layout immediately.
  * *Copy Tool:* Features a select dropdown to copy the layout structure directly from other configured classrooms.
  * *Backend API:* Handles PUT requests at [route.ts](file:///p:/02_projects/mono/apps/erp/app/api/classes/%5Bslug%5D/layout/route.ts) that transactionally deletes obsolete benches and populates newly constructed arrays.

#### 3. Seating Generator Logic & Rules
* **Status:** **0% implemented**.
* **Missing Elements:**
  * No seating allocation algorithm exists in the API routes.
  * The HOD-defined room sequencing filler rules (e.g. `F1 → F2 → F3`) have no database schema storage or visual layout in the frontend.
  * There are no functions/triggers to fetch eligible students based on their `currentSemesterNo` while sequentially ordering them by `College ID`.
  * The anti-cheating bench capacity constraint logic (no two students of the same year per bench, multi-year list exhaustion handling) is not yet written.

